          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no prior psychiatric diagnoses, but her mother recalls a brief period of tearfulness and school refusal approximately two years ago, around the time of her parents' divorce, which resolved without formal intervention. She has no history of hospitalization, self-harm, or prior suicide attempts. She has no known chronic medical conditions and her developmental history was unremarkable. Immunizations are up to date. She had a course of amoxicillin for streptococcal pharyngitis at age 13; she developed a mild maculopapular rash which resolved on discontinuation. Menarche occurred at age 13 and her menstrual cycles are irregular with mild dysmenorrhea. {patientName} has no history of trauma beyond the family disruption associated with the divorce. She does not use tobacco, alcohol, or illicit substances. Baseline sleep was normal until approximately six months ago when progressive insomnia with delayed sleep onset began. Family history is significant for maternal depression and a maternal uncle with bipolar disorder. No prescribed medications prior to this visit; occasional over-the-counter melatonin was used by mother's suggestion for sleep, with partial benefit."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
